entry.title: Ukraine's New Offensive Is Fueled by Captured Russian Weapons
entry.content: Ukraine’s rapid breakthrough in the Kharkiv region a month ago ended up putting hundreds of pieces of Russian armor into Kyiv’s hands, military officials say.

entry.title: Entrenched Positions on Ukraine Dim Hopes of a Resolution
entry.content: As Russian President Vladimir Putin amps up nationalist rhetoric at home and Western leaders deepen their support for Ukraine, the possibility of negotiations to end the conflict appear dim.
